      },
      "preBlockScreens": [
        "Click on the box with the left mouse button.\nTry to hold the button for exactly {bricks.completionParams.target_hold_ms} ms ({bricks.completionParams.target_hold_ms / 1000} s) and then release it.\n\nAfter each click you will see the actual time you held the button for.\n\nThe feedback will be green if you were close to the target time.\n\nIf the feedback is red, you were too fast.\nIf the feedback is blue, you were too slow.\n\nThe block will end after you make 20 clicks."
      ],
      "repeatAfterBlockScreens": [
        "Remember:\nIf the feedback is red, you were too fast.\nIf the feedback is blue, you were too slow.\n\nPress continue when you are ready for the next set of trials."
      ],
      "repeatUntil": {
        "enabled": true,
        "maxAttempts": 3,
        "minTotal": 20,
        "maxMeanMetric": 0.25,
        "metrics": {
          "correctField": "practice_press_results",
          "metricField": "performance_deltas"
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "label": "Practice1",
      "phase": "practice",
      "trials": 4,
      "overrides": {
        "task": {
          "modules": {
            "drt": {
              "enabled": false
            }
          }
        }
      },
      "repeatUntil": {
          "enabled": true,
          "maxAttempts": 3,
          "minMeanMetric": 3,
          "metrics": {
            "correctField": "game.stats.cleared",
            "metricField": "game.stats.cleared"
          }
      },
      "repeatAfterBlockScreens": [
        "Let's have another try.\nRemember: you must click and hold inside the highlighted area as many times as required until the box opens. Do this for each box in turn until all boxes have been opened.\n\nHolding for closer to {bricks.completionParams.target_hold_ms} ms ({bricks.completionParams.target_hold_ms / 1000} s) will clear more of the box.\n"
      ],
      "manipulations": [
        "difficulty_practice",
        "condition_plan"
      ],
      "preBlockScreens": [
        "Great work!\nNow, we will use this same click-and-hold strategy to open some boxes!\n\nIn the following trials, boxes will move slowly along the conveyor belts. You must click and hold for {bricks.completionParams.target_hold_ms} ms ({bricks.completionParams.target_hold_ms / 1000} s) several times on each box, until it opens. You will keep receiving feedback on your clicks throughout but we will no longer show the exact durations.\n\nOnly the highlighted box can be opened. Once you clear a box, another random box will be highlighted.\n\nBy working hard at estimating {bricks.completionParams.target_hold_ms} ms ({bricks.completionParams.target_hold_ms / 1000} s) holds, you can clear the boxes faster and ensure you don't lose coins from boxes being destroyed. Try to open as many boxes as possible to collect more coins!\n\nAfter each trial you will be asked to rate your experienced workload on a scale of 1-10.","In the following block there will be four rounds.\nEach round is a full conveyor trial with multiple boxes followed by the workload questionnaire."
      ],
      "afterBlockScreens": [
        {
          "html": "<div style='font-family: system-ui, -apple-system, sans-serif; font-size: 1.2rem; line-height: 1.45;'>Well done!<p>As part of this experiment, you will also be asked to respond to a flashing stimulus called the \"DRT\".<p>Whenever you see the border of the experiment window flash red, like this:<p><img src='assets/evander-bricks/drt_border.png' alt='DRT example' style='max-width: 480px; width: 100%; height: auto;'/><p>You should press the SPACEBAR as quickly as possible. This will happen repeatedly throughout the conveyor task.<p></div>"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "label": "DRTPractice",
      "phase": "practice",
      "trials": 1,
      "overrides": {
        "display": {
          "ui": {
            "showHUD": false
          },
          "character": {
            "enable": false
          }
        },
        "trial": {
          "mode": "fixed_time",
          "maxTimeSec": 60,
          "endDelayMs": 0,
          "forcedOrder": {
            "enable": false
          }
        },
        "bricks": {
          "initialBricks": {
            "type": "fixed",
            "value": 0
          },
          "forcedSet": [],
          "forcedSetPlan": {
            "enable": false,
            "count": 0
          },
          "maxBricksPerTrial": 0,
          "spawn": {
            "ratePerSec": {
              "type": "fixed",
              "value": 0
            },
            "interSpawnDist": null
          }
        },
        "surveys": {
          "postTrial": []
        }
      },
      "preBlockScreens": [
        "Let's practice the DRT.\nIgnore the conveyor and focus only on the red border signal.\n\nPress SPACEBAR as quickly as possible whenever the border flashes red.\n\nThis block will end after 60 seconds.\n\nWe recommend resting your finger on the SPACEBAR so you can press it quickly without moving your hand.\n\nIn the following block there will be eight rounds."
      ],
      "afterBlockScreens": ["Great job!\n\nWe will now do some practice trials putting both tasks together. Use your mouse to click-and-hold on the highlighted box for {bricks.completionParams.target_hold_ms} ms ({bricks.completionParams.target_hold_ms / 1000} s) several times until it opens, and rest a finger from the other hand on the SPACEBAR. Press the SPACEBAR whenever you see the red border flash, as quickly as you can while still opening the boxes\n\nIt might feel a little tricky to do both tasks at first but we will have several rounds of practice to familiarise you with the responses."]
    },
    {
      "label": "Practice2",
      "phase": "practice",
      "trials": 8,
      "manipulations": [
        "difficulty_practice2",
        "condition_plan"
      ],
      "afterBlockScreens": [
        "Great job! From here on you will always complete both the detection task and the conveyor task.\n\nThe conveyor will change speeds between blocks and sometimes it will be difficult to open all the boxes. You will continue to receive colour-coded feedback on your clicks. Please try your best to open as many boxes as you can within the time limit!\n\nRemember: Opening boxes gives you coins, but boxes being destroyed results in coins being taken away!"
      ]
    },
